{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":220177,"duration_api_ms":220115,"ttft_ms":146616,"num_turns":1,"result":"I'll produce one structured idea record in Critique mode for the active frontier. This is a single research output, not a multi-agent task, so I am not invoking a workflow or editing files; I am returning only the JSON record as required.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"If It Explains Everything, It Predicts Nothing\",\n  \"idea_type\": \"critique\",\n  \"source_basis\": [\n    \"Run mode: Critique. The active frontier (remainder pressure and continuity after self-negation) is saturated with near-duplicate models, so this run pressures the family rather than adding another member.\",\n    \"Primary-text comparison: SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta runs an explicit search-and-negation sequence through the five aggregates and ends in non-clinging, which leaves a live question of what carries non-clinging afterward (https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59/en/bodhi). Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, forbids the seeking mind itself, so no downstream remainder is produced to be located (https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236). The comparison reveals that 'remainder pressure' is generated by the search sequence, not by self-negation as such.\",\n    \"Supporting anomaly text: Dogen, Bendowa, treats practice and realization as one act, so there is no 'after negation' interval in which continuity must be re-housed (notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md).\",\n    \"Thinking-method source: neti-neti negation, used reflexively. I applied it to the research apparatus itself by subtracting every claim that no observation could contradict, then asking what remained. Critique of the method: aggressive negation can discard genuinely useful interpretive heuristics along with empty ones, so it was checked against the frontier brief's own instruction to keep this as a comparative heuristic, not doctrine.\",\n    \"Closest prior art the family inherits: Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind (https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html), and Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition; Talal Asad on discursive tradition; George Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar. These make 'support is constitutively distributed across teachers, texts, vows, institutions' trivially available for any case.\",\n    \"Near-duplicate Lumenary records this critique targets: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Distributed Continuity Architecture, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Continuity Location Under Transformative Practice, The Continuity Ecology of Self-Dissolution, Even No Path Needs Care.\",\n    \"Convergence and divergence with Codex: this converges with Codex's Even No Path Needs Care and The Question Can Make the Distance, which both narrow the no-distance cases; it diverges by attacking the apparatus's falsifiability and inherited explanatory generosity rather than adding another path-coding or question-permission gate.\",\n    \"Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory (loneliness as a real deficit of connection) and modern-human-condition-pew-where-americans-find-meaning-in-life (meaning loss).\"\n  ],\n  \"original_claim\": \"The family of models built around this frontier shares one move that should now be challenged: the claim that continuity, custody, or support is always held somewhere, and that what a path negates predicts where it migrates. This move quietly fuses two different claims. The first is constitutive and trivially true: a transforming person is always sustained by some body, habit, teacher, text, vow, or community, so support can always be found 'relocated' after the fact. This half is inherited from extended-mind reasoning and predicts nothing, because no possible case can contradict it. The second is differential and worth testing: what a path negates predicts where support migrates and how it fails. Only the differential half is a finding, and it has purchase only where a search-and-negation sequence actually runs. In search-refusing paths, where the seeking that generates remainder pressure is itself forbidden (Huangbo), denied a before-and-after (Dogen), or replaced by direct recognition (Dzogchen), there is no remainder to locate; redescribing those traditions' teachers, vows, and communities as 'relocated continuity' is not a confirmation of the model but the visible symptom of its unfalsifiability. Lumenary should therefore narrow the whole continuity-and-remainder apparatus to search-sequence paths, separate the constitutive claim from the differential claim in every record, and refuse to count a model as confirmed unless it names an observation that would show it false in a specific case.\",\n  \"why_it_might_be_new\": \"The frontier has repeatedly listed Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen as anomalies, but each prior model absorbs them by saying the support simply moved to teacher, vow, or present act. The new move is to treat that absorption itself as the diagnostic failure rather than a successful extension: a model whose central concept can swallow every counterexample has stopped doing work. The specific contribution is to name the inherited source of that generosity (extended-mind constitutivity), to separate the trivially true claim from the testable one, and to restrict the testable claim to paths that actually run the negation sequence. This is a falsifiability critique of a model family, not another variable added to it, which is what distinguishes it from the recent question-permission and support-holder findings it otherwise agrees with.\",\n  \"critique\": \"The critique may prove too much. Almost every rich interpretive framework looks unfalsifiable from outside, and the frontier brief itself asks that this work remain a comparative and practitioner-facing heuristic, not a predictive science; demanding a prohibited observation may impose a natural-science standard where it does not belong. A second strain: the differential claim might retain purchase even in search-refusing paths, because those paths show their own characteristic failures (Pure Land warnings against self-power calculation, Dzogchen warnings against reifying recognition). If those failures cluster predictably with what each path refuses, then a support-and-failure frame earns predictive status there too, and my scope-restriction to search-sequence paths is weakened. A third strain: this critique is itself close to Lumenary's own progress-gate and duplicate-production findings, so its novelty is partly recursive, and it should be scored modestly.\",\n  \"epistemic_labels\": [\"textual\", \"interpretive\", \"analogical\", \"speculative\"],\n  \"scores\": {\n    \"novelty\": 0.55,\n    \"generativity\": 0.82,\n    \"cross_tradition_support\": 0.6,\n    \"logical_coherence\": 0.83,\n    \"explanatory_compression\": 0.8,\n    \"empirical_adjacency\": 0.5,\n    \"practice_testability\": 0.7,\n    \"counterargument_quality\": 0.88,\n    \"source_reliability\": 0.7,\n    \"publishability\": 0.6\n  },\n  \"next_research_directions\": [\n    \"If this critique is right, then asking coders to mark, for each continuity model, an observation that would falsify it in a specific case should leave many of the current records with no such observation; those should be retired or downgraded. If coders can readily supply prohibited observations, the family is healthier than claimed and the critique is weakened.\",\n    \"If remainder pressure is produced by the search sequence rather than by self-negation as such, then practitioners moved from a search-and-negation method into a search-refusing method should report the felt question 'what remains / what holds this' fading rather than relocating. If the question persists unchanged across the switch, the sequence-dependence claim is weakened.\",\n    \"Test the scope-restriction directly: code Huangbo, Dogen, and Dzogchen sources for whether their warnings and failures cluster predictably with what each path refuses. If they do, the differential claim has purchase even without a search sequence, and the restriction must be relaxed.\",\n    \"Run a blind distinct-content test against Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Distributed Continuity Architecture, and Operational Remainder Ecology: can readers state what each predicts that the others do not? Records that cannot be distinguished should be merged.\",\n    \"Protocol improvement: in every future comparative model, write the trivially-true constitutive version and the testable differential version as separate sentences before scoring, and refuse novelty credit to the constitutive half.\"\n  ],\n  \"teaching_candidate\": {\n    \"title\": \"Trust What Could Be Proven Wrong\",\n    \"teaching_line\": \"If nothing could show a comfort to be false, it cannot guide you when you most need guidance.\",\n    \"doctrine_claim\": \"An explanation that survives every possible outcome has not explained your situation; before you lean your life on a reassurance, name what would show it untrue.\",\n    \"body\": \"Some sayings feel deep because they can never be wrong. 'You are always held.' 'Nothing is ever truly lacking.' 'It is all unfolding as it should.' These can steady a hard hour, and that is a real use. But a claim that fits every outcome cannot tell you anything about this outcome. When you are deciding what to do, ask a smaller question: what would I expect to see if this were false? If you can name it, the saying is teaching you something. If nothing could ever count against it, treat it as comfort, not counsel, and then go check the plain facts: is there a person you could actually call, a duty you are actually neglecting, a help you are actually avoiding?\",\n    \"target_human_problem\": \"Loneliness and meaning loss soothed by totalizing reassurances that can never be wrong, which feel like understanding while quietly delaying the concrete, awkward act of reaching for real support.\",\n    \"target_cohort\": \"Reflective people who calm distress with all-encompassing spiritual or psychological frames, especially the isolated and the over-managing who prefer a clean explanation to a phone call.\",\n    \"pressure_survived\": \"Survives the search-refusing anomalies (Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen) and the extended-mind near-neighbor by separating what is always true from what tells you about your own case.\",\n    \"falsifying_pressure\": \"Weakens if naming a disproof reliably increases anxiety or strips comfort that a person in acute crisis genuinely needs to stay safe, or if the reassurance was already producing concrete good conduct without any audit. In those cases comfort should not be examined.\",\n    \"status\": \"under_dialogue\",\n    \"tags\": [\"falsifiability\", \"spiritual-bypass\", \"loneliness\", \"meaning-loss\", \"self-negation\", \"critique-mode\"]\n  },\n  \"practice_candidate\": {\n    \"title\": \"Name the Disproof\",\n    \"practice_line\": \"When a reassurance steadies you, name one thing that would show it false, then check whether you actually have concrete support.\",\n    \"purpose\": \"To tell apart a comfort that is guiding you from a comfort that can never be wrong and is therefore quietly substituting for action.\",\n    \"target_human_problem\": \"Loneliness, meaning loss, and the habit of resolving distress with totalizing claims that cannot fail and so cannot prompt a real next step.\",\n    \"target_cohort\": \"Stable, reflective adults who reach for sweeping spiritual or psychological reassurances when alone or under pressure, and who tend to prefer interpretation to contact.\",\n    \"non_fit\": \"Not for acute crisis, fresh grief that needs comfort rather than scrutiny, OCD or scrupulosity where it would become compulsive doubt-checking, psychosis, mania, severe depression, or anyone whose reassurance is the thin thread keeping them safe right now. Not a substitute for clinical care, and not for people already supported by a trusted teacher or community handling this well.\",\n    \"duration\": \"6 minutes\",\n    \"frequency\": \"Only when you notice yourself leaning hard on a sweeping reassurance, no more than twice per week.\",\n    \"minimum_attempt\": \"Try it on three different reassurances over two weeks before judging it, stopping earlier if it increases anxiety or doubt-spiraling.\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      \"Write the reassuring sentence you are leaning on in plain words.\",\n      \"Ask: what would I expect to see, or not see, if this were false? Write one concrete observation.\",\n      \"If you can name one, the saying is doing real work; keep it and act on what it implies.\",\n      \"If nothing could ever count against it, mark it as comfort, not counsel, and do not build a decision on it.\",\n      \"Either way, name one concrete support you actually have access to today: a person to call, a task to finish, a request for help, or a place to go.\",\n      \"Do that one concrete thing, then stop. Do not turn the exercise into an audit of all your beliefs.\"\n    ],\n    \"notice\": [\n      \"Whether the reassurance leads you toward a real person or duty, or only back into your own head.\",\n      \"Whether naming a disproof loosens or tightens the chest.\",\n      \"Whether you are using the saying to avoid an awkward but available act of contact or repair.\"\n    ],\n    \"caution\": \"Stop if this becomes compulsive doubt-checking, increases shame or panic, or strips a comfort you need to stay safe. Comfort in a crisis is not the target; substitution for action is. Seek human or clinical support when distress is high.\",\n    \"weakens_if\": \"It weakens if it increases rumination or anxious certainty-seeking, if it does no better than an ordinary 'who can I reach out to' prompt, or if people use it to dismiss reassurances that were already steadying them into good conduct.\",\n    \"risk_level\": \"low\",\n    \"status\": \"seed\",\n    \"tags\": [\"falsifiability\", \"spiritual-bypass\", \"loneliness\", \"low-risk\", \"contact-first\"]\n  },\n  \"tests\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Unfalsifiability Critique Prior-Art Search\",\n      \"test_type\": \"prior-art\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"Close prior art will exist for the general charge that distributed-cognition and interpretive-tradition accounts are constitutive rather than predictive (philosophy of the extended mind, debates over functionalist over-extension, and Lumenary's own progress-gate and duplicate-production findings), but the specific application that separates a trivially-true constitutive continuity claim from a testable differential one and restricts the latter to search-sequence paths will not already exist as a stated rule. If it does, novelty should fall below 0.35.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Search philosophy of distributed cognition (Clark, Sterelny, Rupert's coupling-constitution objection), Asad and Lindbeck commentary, and the internal records More Is Not The Same As Progress and Restating Is Not Realizing for the exact constitutive-versus-differential distinction.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Do Search-Refusing Paths Predict Their Own Failures\",\n      \"test_type\": \"falsification-attempt\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"If remainder pressure and continuity-location are genuinely sequence-dependent, then search-refusing paths (Huangbo, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct recognition, Pure Land) should not yield a differentiated, predictable map of where support is held and how it fails; their warnings should instead be about refusing the search itself. If blind coding shows these paths produce stable, differentiated support-and-failure clusters tied to what they refuse, the scope-restriction is weakened and the differential claim survives outside search-sequence paths.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Build a small codebook separating refused-search warnings from continuity-location warnings, then blind-code Huangbo, Bendowa, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and Tannisho.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Name the Disproof Two-Week Trial\",\n      \"test_type\": \"practice-report\",\n      \"target_type\": \"practice\",\n      \"prediction\": \"For the named cohort, naming a disproof for a leaned-on reassurance should increase concrete contact and repair actions and reduce the sense that a comfort is substituting for action, without raising anxiety. If it mainly increases doubt-spiraling or performs no better than a plain 'who could I call' prompt, the practice is weakened.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Run a small screened self-report trial against a bare social-support prompt, tracking concrete contact, rumination, anxiety, and whether comfort was examined when it should have been left alone.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Catch-All Explanations Across Domains\",\n      \"test_type\": \"cross-domain\",\n      \"target_type\": \"idea\",\n      \"prediction\": \"In other fields, explanatory frames whose central concept can absorb any outcome (certain over-broad psychodynamic interpretations, some macro-narratives in markets or politics) should fail to predict specific cases despite feeling explanatory. If practitioners who first name a prohibited observation make better case-level predictions than those who do not, the constitutive-versus-differential distinction has cross-domain force.\",\n      \"result\": \"pending\",\n      \"impact\": \"pending\",\n      \"next_action\": \"Collect documented cases where a totalizing explanation accommodated every outcome and compare predictive accuracy when a falsifying observation is required up front.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ee0f54cb-f0fc-49e5-a687-10c3aa48692a","total_cost_usd":2.2173985000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":3636,"cache_creation_input_tokens":301122,"cache_read_input_tokens":16812,"output_tokens":12352,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":301122,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3636,"output_tokens":12352,"cache_read_input_tokens":16812,"cache_creation_input_tokens":301122,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":301122},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":3636,"outputTokens":12352,"cacheReadInputTokens":16812,"cacheCreationInputTokens":301122,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.2173985000000003,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"0a77cda2-39c7-486c-ad4a-88446a02898f"}
